  "notes": "Audit is QUALIFIED on four grounds: (1) $10,709,352 deferred contributions related to TCA should have been recognized as revenue upon acquisition per PSAS; (2) Interest in Mi'gmawei Mawiomi Resources L.P. accounted at cost instead of modified equity method; (3) Interests in Salaweg Inc. and Mi'gmawei Mawiomi Business Corporation Inc. accounted at cost instead of modified equity method; (4) Reserve for purchase of boats ($1,950,000) constitutes a departure from PSAS. Nation is located in Quebec. Consolidated entities include Micmacs Housing Corporation, Gesgapegiag Human Resource Development Commission, Gesgapegiag Natural Resources Inc. and subsidiaries. The deferred revenue balance increased dramatically from $4,968,286 to $12,547,329 causing a large apparent revenue reduction. Net loss of $2,388,257 in 2023 versus surplus of $2,488,639 in 2022."
